==English==

===Etymology===
From Dutch [[mallemerok]], a foolish woman, from [[mal]], foolish, plus French [[marotte]], an object of foolish affection; a [[bauble]].  See [http://www.worldwidewords.org/weirdwords/ww-mal1.htm].

